rComments: My favourite prof in 4 years. I perfected the art of essay-writing in that class, and was so upset he wasn't teaching more courses.

I'm still upset over the fact that he wasn't rehired this year. I keep hoping U of T will change their mind and bring him back, because I want other people to have the chance to see him teach. He was amazing. Engaging, intelligent, enthusiastic and funny. And welcoming and helpful. Nothing but warm feelings about this class.

Professor Gunz is absolutely amazing. He is extremely intelligent, charming, funny and as well, understanding towards his students concerns. I cannot speak more highly of him, it really was a privilege to have been in his class. His lectures were definitely something to look forward to. He made everyone want to succeed. Outstanding.

Outstanding lecturer.  Passionate, motivated, he really tries to push the limits of a standard lecture in terms of content, and not via multimedia or any of that horsefeathery nonsense, but through the spoken content.  He teaches with a focus on personalities in history.
Excellent professor. Fair marker, engaging lecturer, very caring towards his students. He makes you want to be better, do more, and that's a wonderful quality to have.
Amazing prof! Simply AMAZING! Very smart, but also very funny.  His course is a MUST for all IR/HIS majors!
Prof. Gunz is an awesome lecturer -- but I'm still waiting for him to actually come out and say "Think of the Children!"
